column5: Congrats !!
She is so beautiful!  Congrats to your entire family.  Jen
Thanks again to all of you!  jjcanoe
Congratz on the new one it wont be long before there will be nice pics of ya out fishing together cant wait
I am planning to take my 5 yr old son out either friday or Sat so I'll try and post some pics of that.  I might be a little longer in getting the daughter out but it will happen soon.  jjcanoe
Congratulations! Your life is about to change........................for the better
Congrats  When does bass season open?
She is such a cutie! Congrats to you and Linda. Brother John now has someone to antagonize :-)  Good on ya!

When told he was getting a little sister a few months back,  Little John's reply was:  "Well thats OK, as long as she's not annoying like D.W."  Anyone out there with kids under 8 will understand!  jjcanoe

June 10th 2007 3:28 am 6lbs  11oz Kara Yvonne Jackson was born early this morning to very tired, but very happy, parents John and Linda Jackson. Big brother John jr. was also very happy to finally meet his healthy new baby sister a few days early!   Looks like she's dreaming about the bass opener!   Can't wait to get her outfitted with her first rod and reel! Kara and Big Brother John  Kara and Dad   John AKA jjcanoe and Linda, and little John
Congrats man, she looks like a keeper.
AWwwww..congrats....she's a beatiful baby girl!!!  Now that she's here, sorry about the lack of sleep and fishing.....LOL.  Congrats again,  Cliff and BLy
congrats!!  she is a beautiful little angel.  jason
CONGRATS JJCANOE..... She is beautiful.
Excellent catch dude. Congrats.

Thanks everyone!  6lbs 11oz just before the bass opener but I'll definetly keep this one! For those that I've met at the London Swills, you know she definetly gets her looks from mama! Lack of sleep?  I'm a Truck Driver, I get used to it pretty quick!  Lack of fishing?  I had planned to take the boat out for a short cruise today (Sunday) but I think I'll save it for the Sunday of Bass opener.  I already got the OK from the wifey. BTW the above picture contains one of the few things in this world that a truck DOESN'T deliver! (OK maybe the lack of sleep is getting to me)  jjcanoe
awwww cutie!  congrats!  cheers!
Congrats on the beaurty keeper, as for getting out fishing still, take little John with you, the Mrs. might appreciate the break  Maureen
Congrat's again John! She has Linda's looks but your eyes... CLOSED! Gimme a shout if you need a hand setting up the bow-mount baby seat. -Brian
Attaboy John.  Congrats to the entire family and hope everyone is doing great.  Just remember ... ya still have to clean the keepers.
Congrats....I'm gettin' one today!!!  dk

Well then ... I'll offer my congrats to you DK.   Hope all goes well and we'll be waiting for another keeper pic.   With all these new ones being born,   TJ will have to start some type of baby contest.
She's a beauty, congrat's!
Congrads on the new addition !!!!!! She's a real cutie
aawwwww.. sweet..  Nice keeper...congrads
Congrats and all the best to you , mom and the new baby.
Congrats to you and the family! You also Dustin!
Congrats
well done.  our guy was also 6'11 oz when he came last tuesday.
What a little princess. Congrats to you and the Missus!  Cheers, 1leg
Congrats on the beautiful baby girl!!     She's a keeper for sure.  FOTB
Congrats!  Going through this thread, seems like there are lots of lil' anglers being born this month!!

I plan on it! but having a 5 1/2 yr old constantly outfish you takes its toll  Dustin and Pigeonfisher Congrats on yours! We'll have to get a mini fishers league going soon.  How about Team 0.5?  jjcanoe
Congrats, my wife and I will be in the same boat as you in the next few days (due date June 19). We'll have to get together with the little additions and do some infant family fishing. All the best
